<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>AcademeForge</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>AcademeForge</h1>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="#ast">AST</a></li>
                <li><a href="#courses">Programs</a></li>
                <li><a href="#blog">Learning</a></li>
                <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
        <!-- HERO SECTION -->
        <section class="hero">
            <h2>Building Skills, Thinking & Direction — Beyond School Education</h2>
            <p>
                AcademeForge is a learning initiative focused on real-world skills,
                self-growth, and practical learning that traditional education often misses.
            </p>
            <div class="cta-buttons">
                <a href="#ast" class="cta">Explore AST</a>
                <a href="#telegram" class="cta">Join Learning Community</a>
                <a href="#youtube" class="cta">Learn on YouTube</a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- ABOUT / VIDEO -->
        <section class="video" id="about">
            <h3>What is AcademeForge?</h3>
            <p>
                AcademeForge started as an idea in 2024 and is now being rebuilt with clarity.
                Our goal is simple: help learners develop skills, discipline, and practical
                understanding to grow in the digital world.
            </p>
            <p>
                We do not teach school syllabus. We focus on how to learn, how to build,
                and how to apply knowledge in real life.
            </p>
            <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/YOUR_VIDEO_ID" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </section>

        <!-- AST SECTION -->
        <section class="ast" id="ast">
            <h3>AcademeForge Scholars Test (AST)</h3>
            <p>
                The AcademeForge Scholars Test (AST) is an initiative designed to assess
                a learner’s readiness in logic, awareness, and problem-solving.
            </p>
            <p>
                AST is not a traditional exam. It is meant to identify learners who are
                ready for deeper challenges, advanced learning paths, and future opportunities
                within AcademeForge.
            </p>
            <p>
                AST will be conducted in future phases as AcademeForge continues to evolve.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- PROGRAMS -->
        <section class="courses" id="courses">
            <h3>What We Focus On</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Digital & Creative Skills (Editing, Design, Content)</li>
                <li>Technical & Logical Thinking (Coding Basics, Problem Solving)</li>
                <li>Freelancing & Online Work Awareness</li>
                <li>Learning Systems, Focus & Self-Discipline</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                All programs are designed to be short, practical, and output-focused.
                Learning happens by doing, not by memorizing.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- JOURNEY / TRANSPARENCY -->
        <section class="journey">
            <h3>Our Journey</h3>
            <p>
                AcademeForge is currently in a rebuild phase. This phase is focused on
                mastering skills, refining the learning model, and creating meaningful
                content before a full public relaunch.
            </p>
            <p>
                Growth may be invisible right now — but the foundation is being built
                with honesty and intention.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2026 AcademeForge. Rebuilt with clarity and purpose.</p>
    </footer>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>